news.title: Google sues cybercriminal group behind E-ZPass, USPS text phishing scams
news.summary: Google filed a lawsuit against a cybercriminal group largely based in China. The group is behind a massive text message phishing operation, or "smishing"

news.title: Mortgage demand from homebuyers hits highest level since September, despite rising interest rates
news.summary: Homebuyer demand for mortgages climbed last week to the highest level since September. Refinance demand, however, dropped, even though interest rates also rose.

news.title: Swiss sneaker company On raises guidance again, says it won't offer Black Friday deal
news.summary: Swiss sportswear company On blew past Wall Street's expectations as it pledged to offer no discounts during the holiday shopping season. On will not offer any discounts, the company said.

news.title: Autonomous EV trucking company Einride going public in SPAC deal valuing it at $1.8 billion
news.summary: Einride is planning to go public on the NYSE through a SPAC deal with Legato Merger Corp. III valuing it at $1.8 billion.

news.title: Trump is pardoning dozens of allies and backers. Here's who might be seeking clemency
news.summary: Some figures eyed as possible candidates for clemency from President Donald Trump include Ghislaine Maxwell and Sean "Diddy" Combs.

news.title: What typically comes next when the stock market sputters at the start of November
news.summary: The S&P 500 slumped 1.6% last week. But bad first weeks in November usually don't hang over the stock market.

news.title: It might not be Peak Oil after all. What the IEA’s new scenarios mean for oil prices.
news.summary: International agency forecasting energy demand now says the current path will have consumption of oil and gas growing through 2050. Electric-vehicle adoption misses its earlier estimates.

news.title: I’m in my 50s and divorced with a $1.7 million home. I fell in love with an old school friend. Does it make financial sense to marry?
news.summary: “I have a $500,000 Roth IRA, a portfolio account of $ 500,000 and $300,000 in 529 plans,” she says. “I’ve got a lot of money.”

news.title: Where Goldman Sachs says the S&P 500 is headed next year and the next decade
news.summary: Goldman strategists expect the S&P 500 will see annualized gains of 6.5% in the next 10 years. But that's not exactly shooting for the moon.

news.title: U.S. stocks and gold are rallying on hopes that the shutdown ends. What happens once the government reopens?
news.summary: The S&P 500 and gold are both rallying, with stocks nearing a return to record territory. Why the assets could diverge when the shutdown finally ends.
